===Glyph origin===
{{Han etyl}}
{{Han compound|人|東|t1=man|t2=bag|ls=psc|ls2=ic|c1=s|c2=p}} – a man carrying a bag. A glyph {{zh-l|*土|earth}} was later added to show that the bag-carrying man is standing on the ground. From this composition ([[𡍺]]) is the current form. In the modern form, the man on top can be seen as [[亻]] (however, the upper part of the character is unrelated to [[千]]).

See also [[以]], in which a person is carrying something, [[央]], in which a person is carrying a pole, and [[年]], in which a person is carrying the harvest.

===Etymology===
{{zh-ref|Schuessler (2007)}} notes that the etymology is uncertain and compares the word to {{cog|my|စုံ||to be sufficient; pair}}, which STEDT puts under {{inh|zh|sit-pro|*dzum ~ tsum||pair}}.

Pronunciation 3 is the exoactive derivation of pronunciation 1.

